	<div class="comment odd alt depth-2 vcard highlander-comment" id="comment-460640">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-460640" title="Permalink to this comment">19 October, 2015 at 5:58 am</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn">Fred Lunnon</strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d1092312fa69898c042b4042ece9ec8b?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-d1092312fa69898c042b4042ece9ec8b-0">			<p>The subsequent example makes it clear that  Definition 1  should read<br>
“We then model an event {E} by a subset {E_\Omega} of the sample space {\Omega}.”<br>
or more readably<br>
“We then model events {E} by subsets {E_\Omega} of the sample space {\Omega}.”</p>
<p><i>[Corrected, thanks – T.]</i></p>
