		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/887771945e51a7ec4149d7a8a0c82e94?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-887771945e51a7ec4149d7a8a0c82e94-0">			<p>Dear Terrence:</p>
<p>Have you read or browsed ‘Probability: The Logic of Science’ by the late physicist E.T. Jaynes, and if so, what did you think of it, and would you ever consider using it for parts of such a course?</p>
<p>Sincerely,<br>
James</p>
