	<div class="comment byuser comment-author-teorth bypostauthor odd alt depth-2 vcard highlander-comment" id="comment-460004">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-460004" title="Permalink to this comment">2 October, 2015 at 1:01 pm</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn"><a href="http://www.math.ucla.edu/~tao" rel="external nofollow" class="url">Terence Tao</a></strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3c795880f3b73784a9b75fbff3772701?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-3c795880f3b73784a9b75fbff3772701-2">			<p><img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5COmega&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="\Omega" title="\Omega" class="latex"> is used here as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Synecdoche" rel="nofollow">synecdoche</a>, which is a standard convention in mathematics when referring to a structured space.  For instance a group is formally a tuple <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28G%2C+%5Ccdot%2C+e%2C+%28%29%5E%7B-1%7D%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="(G, \cdot, e, ()^{-1})" title="(G, \cdot, e, ()^{-1})" class="latex"> consisting of a set <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=G&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="G" title="G" class="latex"> together with various operations on it, but we usually abbreviate it via synecdoche as just <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=G&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="G" title="G" class="latex">, thus by abuse of notation <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=G+%3D+%28G%2C+%5Ccdot%2C+e%2C+%28%29%5E%7B-1%7D%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="G = (G, \cdot, e, ()^{-1})" title="G = (G, \cdot, e, ()^{-1})" class="latex">.  Similarly for vector spaces, topological spaces, rings, fields, manifolds, metric spaces, etc..</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_460004" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_460004" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">15</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_460004" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_460004">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460004_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px; text-align: left; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #;">Rate This</div><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; clear: both;"></p></div>
<script type="text/javascript" charset="UTF-8"><!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--
PDRTJS_settings_132742_comm_460004={"id":132742,"unique_id":"wp-comment-460004","title":"%24latex%20Omega%24%20is%20used%20here%20as%20a%20%26lt%3Ba%20HREF%3D%26quot%3Bhttps%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FSynecdoche%26quot%3B%20rel%3D%26quot%3Bnofollow%26quot%3B%26gt%3Bsynecdoche%26lt%3B%2Fa%26gt%3B%2C%20which%20is%20a%20standard%20convention%20in%20mathematics%20when%20referring%20to%20a%20structured%20spa...","permalink":"https:\/\/terrytao.wordpress.com\/2015\/09\/29\/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory\/#comment-460004","item_id":"_comm_460004"};
