	<div class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 vcard highlander-comment" id="comment-460032">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-460032" title="Permalink to this comment">2 October, 2015 at 5:09 pm</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn"><a href="http://icpr.itam.mx" rel="external nofollow" class="url">Tapen Sinha</a></strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/dbcca3cd10910f56aa0f1e15bcad15c6?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-dbcca3cd10910f56aa0f1e15bcad15c6-0">			<p>Jumping from the finitely additive probabilities to the countably additive ones looks deceptively simple but it is not. Rajeeva Karandikar has a beautiful lecture on the subject. He should know. He has done some deep work on that matter.<br>
<a href="http://math.iisc.ernet.in/~imi/downloads/LimitTheoremsFinitelyAdditiveProbability3.pdf" rel="nofollow">http://math.iisc.ernet.in/~imi/downloads/LimitTheoremsFinitelyAdditiveProbability3.pdf</a></p>
<p>Tapen Sinha</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_460032" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_460032" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">1</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_460032" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_460032">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460032_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px;