	<div class="comment even depth-3 vcard parent highlander-comment" id="comment-460076">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-460076" title="Permalink to this comment">3 October, 2015 at 5:56 pm</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn">Rex</strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/255c68cc6b792a6614a9f9a60a2e725f?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-255c68cc6b792a6614a9f9a60a2e725f-1">			<p>Would you have an example to illustrate this irreversibility for sample spaces?</p>
<p>As for base change, it is not clear to me what the invariant thing that schemes under different bases are modeling. One guess would be the underlying defining equations. However, I usually see it done the other way: that the defining equations are models giving a concrete realization of a variety in affine space.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_460076" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_460076" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">1</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_460076" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_460076">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460076_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px; text-align: left; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #;">Rate This</div><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; clear: both;"></p></div>
<script type="text/javascript" charset="UTF-8"><!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--
PDRTJS_settings_132742_comm_460076={"id":132742,"unique_id":"wp-comment-460076","title":"Would%20you%20have%20an%20example%20to%20illustrate%20this%20irreversibility%20for%20sample%20spaces%3FAs%20for%20base%20change%2C%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20to%20me%20what%20the%20invariant%20thing%20that%20schemes%20under%20different%20bases%20are%20modeling.%20...","permalink":"https:\/\/terrytao.wordpress.com\/2015\/09\/29\/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory\/#comment-460076","item_id":"_comm_460076"};
