	<div class="comment even depth-5 vcard parent highlander-comment" id="comment-460139">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-460139" title="Permalink to this comment">4 October, 2015 at 4:04 pm</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn">Rex</strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/255c68cc6b792a6614a9f9a60a2e725f?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-255c68cc6b792a6614a9f9a60a2e725f-2">			<p>At first I thought I understood what the “object vs model” analogy you were trying to describe is, but now I’m not so sure.</p>
<p>Are you saying that a fixed sample space is something like an finite-level approximation of some ultimate (perhaps non-mathematical) “space” of all possible outcomes (including future experiments we have not yet decided to perform or record)? In the same way that, say, the <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=p&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="p" title="p" class="latex">-adic integers can be “modeled” by the projections to its finite quotients <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5Cmathbf%7BZ%7D%2Fp%5En+%5Cmathbf%7BZ%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="\mathbf{Z}/p^n \mathbf{Z}" title="\mathbf{Z}/p^n \mathbf{Z}" class="latex">?</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_460139" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_460139" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">1</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_460139" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_460139">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460139_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px; text-align: left; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #;">Rate This</div><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; clear: both;"></p></div>
<script type="text/javascript" charset="UTF-8"><!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--
PDRTJS_settings_132742_comm_460139={"id":132742,"unique_id":"wp-comment-460139","title":"At%20first%20I%20thought%20I%20understood%20what%20the%20%26quot%3Bobject%20vs%20model%26quot%3B%20analogy%20you%20were%20trying%20to%20describe%20is%2C%20but%20now%20I%26%23039%3Bm%20not%20so%20sure.Are%20you%20saying%20that%20a%20fixed%20sample%20space%20is%20something%20like%20an%20finite-lev...","permalink":"https:\/\/terrytao.wordpress.com\/2015\/09\/29\/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory\/#comment-460139","item_id":"_comm_460139"};
