	</div>
	
	<div class="comment byuser comment-author-teorth bypostauthor odd alt depth-5 vcard highlander-comment" id="comment-460144">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-460144" title="Permalink to this comment">4 October, 2015 at 4:21 pm</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn"><a href="http://www.math.ucla.edu/~tao" rel="external nofollow" class="url">Terence Tao</a></strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3c795880f3b73784a9b75fbff3772701?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-3c795880f3b73784a9b75fbff3772701-5">			<p>Yes, I think this is a good way to think about things.  In principle one could try to pass to an inverse limit of “all” sample spaces to work in some “universal” sample space, but one would have to exit the category of sets to do so, in order to avoid Russell type paradoxes, so this seems like more trouble than it is worth.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_460144" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_460144" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">2</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_460144" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_460144">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_460144_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px; text-align: left; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #;">Rate This</div><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; clear: both;"></p></div>
<script type="text/javascript" charset="UTF-8"><!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--
