		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/979861f7ba3c0a0b30791ed8810883be?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-979861f7ba3c0a0b30791ed8810883be-0">			<p>In Exercise 28, in the first sentence it looks like the words “real line” are extraneous.  In part (iv), I think you’re missing a factor of <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28-1%29%5En&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="(-1)^n" title="(-1)^n" class="latex">.  Possibly you might also want to add a hint that the formula represents the measure of a box in <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=R%5En&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="R^n" title="R^n" class="latex">.</p>
