		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/08dfd2c5aa89cf1f8d1051ea33813b9c?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-08dfd2c5aa89cf1f8d1051ea33813b9c-0">			<p>Dear professor Tao,</p>
<p>In definition 1 and in definition 22, the the meaning of “to model something by something else” is not clear to me. In particular are you saying that the measurable subsets are called events, or are you saying something else?</p>
