<ul class="children">
	
	<div class="comment byuser comment-author-teorth bypostauthor even depth-2 vcard parent highlander-comment" id="comment-467818">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-467818" title="Permalink to this comment">19 April, 2016 at 9:47 am</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn"><a href="http://www.math.ucla.edu/~tao" rel="external nofollow" class="url">Terence Tao</a></strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3c795880f3b73784a9b75fbff3772701?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-3c795880f3b73784a9b75fbff3772701-10">			<p>Abstract probability spaces are discussed in Section 4 of the blog post.  Alternatively, one can eschew axiomatisation algoether, and simply define an abstract probability space to be a structure of events and probabilities that has at least one concrete model.  This would be analogous to defining (say) a group to be an object with a multiplication operation that had at least one concrete representation as an action; indeed, this is close to how groups were first viewed historically.  (In this particular case, Cayley’s theorem tells us that the two definitions of a group are equivalent.)</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_467818" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_467818" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">4</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_467818" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_467818">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_467818_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px; text-align: left; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #;">Rate This</div><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; clear: both;"></p></div>
