	<div class="comment odd alt depth-5 vcard highlander-comment" id="comment-474386">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-474386" title="Permalink to this comment">15 November, 2016 at 5:00 am</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn">Anonymous</strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-false-13">			<p>I think it is clear now. I find the linked article of the Kolmogrov axioms (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability_axioms" rel="nofollow">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Probability_axioms</a>) is actually very confusing. If one checks the Axiom Three there, one can see that individual events are described as sets while they do not have to be as you pointed out. At least one should notice that those events in the event space do not have to be subsets of the probability space <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%5COmega&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="\Omega" title="\Omega" class="latex"> at all.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_474386" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_474386" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">1</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_474386" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_474386">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_474386_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px;