	<div class="comment even thread-even depth-1 vcard parent highlander-comment" id="comment-469921">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-469921" title="Permalink to this comment">20 June, 2016 at 8:14 am</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn">Confused Robitaille</strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-false-15">			<p>I’m also not sure how well your analogy to linear algebra is, because of different levels of abstractions used in the definition of real vector space vs. real vector space model resp. abstract probability space (in the sense that you mentioned of Kolmogorffs axioms + sigma-algebra version of Boolean algebra axioms) vs. probability space (as in Definition 19):<br>
Real vector spaces are abstract, but representations of them are concrete, in the sense each representation is a fixed set built out of numbers that one could write down. But abstract probability spaces and probability spaces are both abstract, because the latter is not a concrete set that one could write down, but itself a set that is given abstractly by axioms that characterize it.</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_469921" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_469921" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">1</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_469921" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_469921">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_469921_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px; text-align: left; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #;">Rate This</div><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; clear: both;"></p></div>
<script type="text/javascript" charset="UTF-8"><!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--
PDRTJS_settings_132742_comm_469921={"id":132742,"unique_id":"wp-comment-469921","title":"I%26%23039%3Bm%20also%20not%20sure%20how%20well%20your%20analogy%20to%20linear%20algebra%20is%2C%20because%20of%20different%20levels%20of%20abstractions%20used%20in%20the%20definition%20of%20real%20vector%20space%20vs.%20real%20vector%20space%20model%20resp.%20abstract%20pr...","permalink":"https:\/\/terrytao.wordpress.com\/2015\/09\/29\/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory\/#comment-469921","item_id":"_comm_469921"};
