	<div class="comment even depth-2 vcard parent highlander-comment" id="comment-476804">
		<div class="comment-metadata">
			<p class="comment-permalink"><a href="https://terrytao.wordpress.com/2015/09/29/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory/#comment-476804" title="Permalink to this comment">16 January, 2017 at 11:30 am</a></p>
			<p class="comment-author"><strong class="fn">Anonymous</strong></p>
					</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			<img alt="" src="https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=32&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=PG" class="avatar avatar-32 grav-hashed grav-hijack" height="32" width="32" id="grav-false-22">			<p>Sorry for the wrong question above.</p>
<p> In Example 3, it is said that “Now suppose that we wish to roll the die again to obtain a second random variable $\latex {Y}$. ” At this point, do we implicitly <i>assume</i> that <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Y&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="Y" title="Y" class="latex"> is independent of <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=X&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="X" title="X" class="latex"> so that we define later <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Y_%7B%5COmega%27%7D%28i%2Cj%29%3Dj&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="Y_{\Omega'}(i,j)=j" title="Y_{\Omega'}(i,j)=j" class="latex"> or do we have to see by <i>calculation</i> (via the definition of <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=X_%7B%5COmega%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="X_{\Omega'}" title="X_{\Omega'}" class="latex"> and <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Y_%7B%5COmega%27%7D&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="Y_{\Omega'}" title="Y_{\Omega'}" class="latex">) of the joint distribution of <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=%28X%2CY%29&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="(X,Y)" title="(X,Y)" class="latex">  that <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=X&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="X" title="X" class="latex"> and <img src="https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=Y&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=545454&amp;s=0" alt="Y" title="Y" class="latex"> are indeed independent?</p>
<div class="pd-rating" id="pd_rating_holder_132742_comm_476804" style="display: inline-block;"><div class="rating-icons" id="pd_rate_132742_comm_476804" style="float:left;"><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804.rate(1);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804.hover(1);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804_nero_1" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom left; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804_msg_1" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div><div class="rating-nero-icon" onmouseout="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804.rebuild();" onclick="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804.rate(2);" onmouseover="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804.hover(2);" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804_nero_2" style="background-size: 32px 32px !important; cursor: pointer; width: 16px; height: 16px;  line-height: 16px; background: url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/nero-hand-sml.png) bottom right; float: left; padding: 0px; margin: 0px; margin: 0px;">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-nero-value" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804_msg_2" style="text-align: center; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #; float:left; padding: 0px 4px;">0</div></div><span style="float:left;">&nbsp;</span><div id="rating_info_132742_comm_476804" style="display:block;float:left;background:url(https://polldaddy.com/images/ratings/info.png) no-repeat 3px 2px;width:16px;height:16px;cursor:pointer; null " onclick="javascript:PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804.togglePopup();return false;"><span style="display:none;">i</span></div><div class="pd_popup_holder" id="pd_popup_holder_132742_comm_476804">&nbsp;</div><div class="rating-msg" id="PDRTJS_132742_comm_476804_msg" style="float:left; padding-left: 5px; text-align: left; font:normal normal /16px ; color: #;">Rate This</div><p style="padding: 0px; margin: 0px; clear: both;"></p></div>
<script type="text/javascript" charset="UTF-8"><!--//--><![CDATA[//><!--
PDRTJS_settings_132742_comm_476804={"id":132742,"unique_id":"wp-comment-476804","title":"Sorry%20for%20the%20wrong%20question%20above.%20In%20Example%203%2C%20it%20is%20said%20that%20%26quot%3BNow%20suppose%20that%20we%20wish%20to%20roll%20the%20die%20again%20to%20obtain%20a%20second%20random%20variable%20%24latex%20%7BY%7D%24.%20%26quot%3B%20At%20this%20point%2C%20do%20we%20implicitl...","permalink":"https:\/\/terrytao.wordpress.com\/2015\/09\/29\/275a-notes-0-foundations-of-probability-theory\/#comment-476804","item_id":"_comm_476804"};
